SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 691
By Crowe
A RESOLUTION to honor the memory of Robert Chris "Bob"
Carroll of Johnson City.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly were greatly saddened to learn of
the passing of Robert Chris "Bob" Carroll of Johnson City; and
WHEREAS, Bob Carroll was an exemplary public servant and consummate professional
who worked assiduously to improve the quality of life for his fellow citizens in numerous
capacities; and
WHEREAS, born on April 24, 1954, in Johnson City, Mr. Carroll was the son of Dewey
and Jessie Dunn Carroll; and
WHEREAS, upon graduating from Happy Valley High School, Bob Carroll served in the
United States Air Force during the Vietnam Era; he was then employed by the Carter County
School System as a bus driver for forty years; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Carroll faithfully served the people of Carter County as a constable for
the 8th District after being elected in 1974, dedicating over five decades to public safety and
community service; and
WHEREAS, Bob Carroll held leadership roles within the Tennessee Constable
Association, including two terms as executive director and CEO, and was a founding member of
the West Carter County Volunteer Fire Department, beginning his service in 1971; and
WHEREAS, his service extended far beyond his official duties to working as a
courthouse bailiff, organizing a community watch, checking in on elderly residents, volunteering
with Second Harvest Food Bank, and remaining deeply involved in his church and faith; and
SJR0691
012706
- 1 -

WHEREAS, Mr. Carroll completed countless hours of law enforcement and firefighting
training, including hazmat and safe schools instruction, always striving to go above and beyond;
and
WHEREAS, at the 2025 Tennessee Constable Association Annual Convention, Bob
Carroll was honored with the Frankie Lax Sr. Award, the organization's highest recognition,
awarded to a constable who exemplifies leadership, service, and dedication to both the
community and fellow public servants; and
WHEREAS, in addition to his public service, Mr. Carroll was a devoted thirty-year
member of Hampton Masonic Lodge #750 and Jericho Shrine Temple, as well as a member of
Sinking Creek Baptist Church; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Carroll was deeply devoted to his family, and he endeavored to remain
true to family values of the highest order; and
WHEREAS, Bob Carroll is survived by his wife, Lynn Henson Carroll; his children, Chris
(Kim) Carroll, Cynthia Fenner, April Fenner, Candi Carroll and friend, Joel Etter, Alex (Tara)
Carroll, and Jessie (Brandon) Hodges; twelve grandchildren; his brother, Lynn (Sandra) Carroll;
his brother-in-law, Ted Mynatt; and several nieces and nephews; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Carroll was preceded in death by his parents and his sister, Shirley
Mynatt; and
WHEREAS, it is most fitting that the members of this General Assembly should pause to
remember the bountiful life of this exceptional public servant and human being; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor the memory of Robert Chris "Bob" Carroll,
reflecting fondly upon his impeccable character and his stalwart commitment to living the
examined life with courage and conviction.
- 2 - 012706

BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that we express our sympathy and offer our condolences
to the family of Mr. Carroll.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
